    {
      "id": "3d7c49a9e8d2d506f4d63b31d66a58cca1947e71",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 147,
        "name": "Maloo",
        "email": "maloo@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "maloo",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2013-04-08 23:07:25.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nTests received by maloo, run on CentOS release 6.3/x86_64: (https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/4b4c2840-a099-11e2-923c-52540035b04c).  Ran 16 tests.  5 tests failed: sanity-quota, replay-ost-single, recovery-small, replay-single, sanityn.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "6ef418b350aa23d4c0026f6b35bcf59dd193b90c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-09 08:07:53.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: Looks good to me, approved\n\nAlex, two reasons for this change:\n- the in-use directory should not show nlink=0 to callers, since this can mistakenly cause callers to think the directory is unlinked (e.g. potentially LU-3022)\n- it better matches the ext4 upstream implementation, which was fixed for similar reasons",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "b2c3fbca876a0da10c36180291d20837246cb2e4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-09 08:13:40.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nhmm, sorry don't get it. nlink can reach 0 exactly when the directory is unlinked?\ni'd rather think having nlink > 0 when the directory is on /PENDING isn't good?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "e357ffd0d3af0fce74f979f62aee04e238b65adf",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-10 23:17:07.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: (1 inline comment)\n\nAlex, problem can happen because directory with many subdirs has nlinks=1, so if nlink is decremented temporarily to 0 and then incremented afterward it is possible to expose nlink==0 to some callers. \n\nThe patch changes this to not decrement in the nlink==1 case at all.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "17fdb50e6411dcf43f8cde44a0f43b895f585192",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2013-04-11 03:31:58.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: Looks good to me, but someone else must approve\n\nok, thanks for explanation.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
